<subSubSection id="C33502C489304B34D5CBFA78FC8EFE81" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="136" pageId="3" pageNumber="135" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B90514F89304B34D5CBFA78FB25FF65" blockId="3.[151,1436,1516,2010]" lastBlockId="4.[151,1437,151,645]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="136" pageId="3" pageNumber="135">
<emphasis id="B95B8D5D89304B33D5CBFA78FE90F998" bold="true" box="[199,365,1516,1541]" pageId="3" pageNumber="135">Redescription</emphasis>
. (
<specimenCount id="9D299AC689304B33D48BFA79FE60F998" box="[391,413,1517,1541]" pageId="3" pageNumber="135" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
) Body length 6.5–7.0 mm. 
<emphasis id="B95B8D5D89304B33D7D3FA78FCCFF998" bold="true" box="[735,818,1516,1541]" pageId="3" pageNumber="135">Colour</emphasis>
. Body integument brownish black; vestiture of elytra consisting of short, rounded, recumbent, overlapping scales, slightly longer that wide, concealing integument in fresh specimens, forming shades of whitish yellow and brownish colour, basal and apical thirds of elytra paler, medium third with a darker transverse band. 
<emphasis id="B95B8D5D89304B33D7B7F9CDFD07F9EF" bold="true" box="[699,762,1625,1650]" pageId="3" pageNumber="135">Head</emphasis>
. Rostrum longer than head plus prothorax, thin, evenly narrowing from base to insertion of antennae, sides parallel in apical half, moderately downcurved, punctate and covered by scales in basal third, smooth and shiny in medium and apical thirds, transverse furrow at base of rostrum reduced, concealed by scales, head short; antennae with segments 1 and 2 subequal in length, 1 as long as 3+4. 
<emphasis id="B95B8D5D89304B33D5DEF97DFEB1F89F" bold="true" box="[210,332,1769,1794]" pageId="3" pageNumber="135">Prothorax</emphasis>
. Wider than long, widest and rounded in apical third, sides almost straight in basal half, densely punctate, median line present, visible through scales, scales brown with paler spots on sides. 
<emphasis id="B95B8D5D89304B33D1ABF899FB0EF8BB" bold="true" box="[1191,1267,1805,1830]" pageId="3" pageNumber="135">Elytra</emphasis>
. Twice as long as wide (ratio w/l: 0.55), sides subparallel in basal two thirds, rounded in apical third, humeri raised, declivital callosities present at apex of interstria 3, followed by a strong depression, striae narrow, interstriae flat and wide; scutellum small, shiny and flat. 
<emphasis id="B95B8D5D89304B33D4F3F8EDFD8EF80F" bold="true" box="[511,627,1913,1938]" pageId="3" pageNumber="135">Abdomen</emphasis>
. Underside covered by pale brownish scales, ventrites 1 and 2 elongate and subequal, 2 as long as 3–5. 
<emphasis id="B95B8D5D89304B33D4FBF809FDD2F82B" bold="true" box="[503,559,1949,1974]" pageId="3" pageNumber="135">Legs</emphasis>
. Femora clavate, armed with a strong ventral tooth; tibiae straight, armed with a strong ventral tooth proximally near middle; tarsi reddish. 
<emphasis id="B95B8D5D89304B33D64BF855FC48F847" bold="true" box="[839,949,1985,2010]" pageId="3" pageNumber="135">Genitalia</emphasis>
. Penis short (ratio w/l: 0.5), sides straight, subparallel, converging near apex, apex truncate, slightly and regularly curved in lateral view (
<figureCitation id="13144DCA89374B34D1C2FF03FAD7FF2D" box="[1230,1322,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1565,1587]" captionTargetBox="[189,1409,396,1528]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[151,1436,373,1544]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 6. Penis of Afrosmicronyx species, dorsal (left) and lateral (right) view. A. Afrosmicronyx giganteus (Hustache), specimen from Cameroon. B. A. quadrituberculatus (Hustache), lectotype. C. A. sopubiae (Marshall), lectotype. D. A. angolanus (Hustache), holotype. E. A. maerens (Marshall), lectotype. F. A. dorsomaculatus (Cox), specimen from Mauritania. G. A.mirei sp.n., holotype.H.A.armipes (Voss),holotype.I. A.madagascariensis sp. n., holotype.J.A.umbrinus (Hustache), specimen from Cameroon.Scale bar = 200 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1117518/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="136">
Fig. 6 
<collectingRegion id="49EB9FAD89374B34D01FFF03FAD7FF2D" box="[1299,1322,151,176]" country="Nigeria" name="Rivers" pageId="4" pageNumber="136">A</collectingRegion>
</figureCitation>
). Females are distinguished from males by their slightly longer ventral tooth on tibiae, by their rostrum, which is less coarsely punctate in apical half, and by the insertion of their antennae on rostrum, which nearer to middle.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B90514F89374B34D5CBFE90FC8EFE81" blockId="4.[151,1437,151,645]" box="[199,883,260,285]" pageId="4" pageNumber="136">
<emphasis id="B95B8D5D89374B34D5CBFE90FEADFE80" bold="true" box="[199,336,260,285]" pageId="4" pageNumber="136">Life history</emphasis>
. Unknown. Adults collected in July and August.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C33502C489374B34D5CBFEB3FDDBFEDD" box="[199,550,295,320]" pageId="4" pageNumber="136" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8B90514F89374B34D5CBFEB3FDDBFEDD" blockId="4.[151,1437,151,645]" box="[199,550,295,320]" pageId="4" pageNumber="136">
<emphasis id="B95B8D5D89374B34D5CBFEB3FEA4FEDD" bold="true" box="[199,345,295,320]" pageId="4" pageNumber="136">Distribution</emphasis>
. 
<collectingCountry id="F33811DF89374B34D46BFEBCFE22FEDD" box="[359,479,296,320]" name="Cameroon" pageId="4" pageNumber="136">Cameroon</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F33811DF89374B34D4E6FEB3FDDFFEDD" box="[490,546,295,320]" name="Serbia" pageId="4" pageNumber="136">Mali</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C33502C489374B34D5CBFED8FC3DFD19" pageId="4" pageNumber="136" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B90514F89374B34D5CBFED8FC3DFD19" blockId="4.[151,1437,151,645]" pageId="4" pageNumber="136">
<emphasis id="B95B8D5D89374B34D5CBFED8FEB8FEF8" bold="true" box="[199,325,332,357]" pageId="4" pageNumber="136">Discussion</emphasis>
. Hustache’s description of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2F2ACC89374B34D775FED8FC6CFEF9" baseAuthorityName="Hustache" baseAuthorityYear="1935" box="[633,913,332,356]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Afrosmicronyx" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="136" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="giganteus">
<emphasis id="B95B8D5D89374B34D775FED8FC6CFEF9" box="[633,913,332,356]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="136">Afrosmicronyx giganteus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was based on a single specimen, from Sokolo (“ 
<collectingCountry id="F33811DF89374B34D5A5FEFBFF09FE15" box="[169,244,367,392]" name="Sudan" pageId="4" pageNumber="136">Sudan</collectingCountry>
” [
<collectingCountry id="F33811DF89374B34D402FEFBFEB7FE15" box="[270,330,367,392]" name="Serbia" pageId="4" pageNumber="136">Mali</collectingCountry>
], 
<date id="FF91778F89374B34D451FEFBFE42FE15" box="[349,447,367,392]" pageId="4" pageNumber="136" value="1933-07">vii-1933</date>
, Hustache 1935). This species is by far the largest of the genus and cannot be confused with any other species. Despite intensive search, the specimen used by Hustache for the description of the species was not found in the 
<collectionCode id="ED3EC98A89374B34D491FE2CFE0FFE52" box="[413,498,440,463]" country="France" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34988" name="Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle" pageId="4" pageNumber="136">MNHN</collectionCode>
collections. However, in the Rema.coll there is a specimen from Dogo (
<collectingCountry id="F33811DF89374B34D051FE23FA68FE4D" box="[1373,1429,439,464]" name="Serbia" pageId="4" pageNumber="136">Mali</collectingCountry>
) identified as 
<taxonomicName id="4C2F2ACC89374B34D422FE49FE5EFE69" authorityName="Haran &amp; Perrin" authorityYear="2017" box="[302,419,477,500]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Smicronyx" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="136" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B95B8D5D89374B34D422FE49FE5EFE69" box="[302,419,477,500]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="136">Smicronyx</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<emphasis id="B95B8D5D89374B34D4BAFE49FD68FE69" box="[438,661,476,500]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="136">
s. g. 
<taxonomicName id="4C2F2ACC89374B34D4FEFE48FD68FE69" authorityName="Hustache" authorityYear="1935" box="[498,661,476,500]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Afrosmicronyx" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="136" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Afrosmicronyx</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
) 
<taxonomicName id="4C2F2ACC89374B34D7A4FE49FCE8FE69" baseAuthorityName="Hustache" baseAuthorityYear="1935" box="[680,789,477,500]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Afrosmicronyx" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="136" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="giganteus">
<emphasis id="B95B8D5D89374B34D7A4FE49FCE8FE69" box="[680,789,477,500]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="136">giganteus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<collectingRegion id="49EB9FAD89374B34D649FE48FCA1FE69" box="[837,860,476,500]" country="Nigeria" name="Rivers" pageId="4" pageNumber="136">A</collectingRegion>
. Hoffmann, with the indication “comparison with 
<typeStatus id="5494EFED89374B34D59BFD94FF31FD85" box="[151,204,512,536]" pageId="4" pageNumber="136">type</typeStatus>
”. 
<collectingRegion id="49EB9FAD89374B34D5EDFD94FF05FD85" box="[225,248,512,536]" country="Nigeria" name="Rivers" pageId="4" pageNumber="136">A</collectingRegion>
. Hoffmann has created confusions by transferring several 
<typeStatus id="5494EFED89374B34D68CFD94FC46FD85" box="[896,955,512,536]" pageId="4" pageNumber="136">types</typeStatus>
of Hustache to his collection (
<bibRefCitation id="EFBE2CBE89374B34D002FE6BFA69FD85" author="Perrin" box="[1294,1428,511,536]" pageId="4" pageNumber="136" refString="Perrin, H. (1998) Les types des especes afrotropicales du genre Curculio Linne, 1758 (Coleoptera, Curculionidae). Revue francaise d'Entomologie, 20 (4), 135 - 141." type="journal article" year="1998">Perrin 1998</bibRefCitation>
) and relabeling them. But since this specimen was found in the Rema.coll it is not likely a transfer of 
<collectingRegion id="49EB9FAD89374B34D00BFDB0FAE3FDA1" box="[1287,1310,548,572]" country="Nigeria" name="Rivers" pageId="4" pageNumber="136">A</collectingRegion>
. Hoffmann in this case. In the absence of available 
<typeStatus id="5494EFED89374B34D75CFDDCFD7DFDFD" box="[592,640,584,608]" pageId="4" pageNumber="136">type</typeStatus>
material, and given the need to provide a 
<typeStatus id="5494EFED89374B34D158FDDCFB79FDFD" box="[1108,1156,584,608]" pageId="4" pageNumber="136">type</typeStatus>
for this nominal species, we designated this specimen as the 
<typeStatus id="5494EFED89374B34D729FDF9FD83FD18" box="[549,638,621,645]" pageId="4" pageNumber="136">neotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2F2ACC89374B34D7AFFDF8FC47FD19" baseAuthorityName="Hustache" baseAuthorityYear="1935" box="[675,954,620,644]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Afrosmicronyx" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="136" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="giganteus">
<emphasis id="B95B8D5D89374B34D7AFFDF8FC47FD19" box="[675,954,620,644]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="136">Afrosmicronyx giganteus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
